FlowInterviewLog.name: FlowInterviewLog
FlowInterviewLog.description: Represents the logs of a screen flow interview. An interview is an instance of a running or previously run flow.

FlowInterviewGuid.description: Globally unique identifier for the interview.

FlowLabel.description: The flow’s label. Only shows up in API results when users query FlowInterviewLog, or when they include this field in a report.

FlowNamespace.description: Namespace of the flow interview logged in the FlowInterviewLog.

FlowVersionNumber.description: The number of the flow version for a flow definition. Flow versions are counted sequentially from 1.

InterviewDurationInMinutes.description: Total number of minutes between InterviewStartTimestamp and InterviewEndTimestamp, even if flow interview is paused.

InterviewEndTimestamp.description: The date and time when the interview ended.

InterviewStartTimestamp.description: The date and time when the interview started.

InterviewStatus.description: Status of the interview. Valid values are: Autosaved—This value is available in API version 62.0 and later. Completed Error Expired—This value is available in API version 62.0 and later. Paused Running VersionPaused—This value is available in API version 60.0 and later.

Name.description: Autogenerated name of the flow interview log record.

OwnerId.description: The user who owns the FlowInterviewLog record. This field is a polymorphic relationship field.
